adjectives.description: unaccustomed (comparative more unaccustomed, superlative most unaccustomed)

entries.meaning: Not used to an event or thing, not accustomed.
examples: I again conveyed his key into his pocket, and counterfeiting sleep—though I never once closed my eyes, lay in bed till after he arose and went to prayers—an exercise to which I had long been unaccustomed.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of unaccustom
